column12: G02Q15. Instructions - Please read carefully     You will now be played audio samples one after the other. Please listen to each sample and make the following two evaluations each time:  Unacceptability, which refers to your personal assessment of the extent to which an utterance is still permissible. Please rate the level of unacceptability of the audio sample by moving the slider from left (less unacceptable) to right (more unacceptable) to the position that you find most appropriate.  Demand for Consequences, which aims to measure the degree to which an utterance is (not) tolerable with respect to your understanding of social norms, conventions, and values. In other words, how strongly the audio sample calls for social or legal repercussions to the detriment of the author or speaker due to the violation of social norms or values. Please rate the demand for consequences of the audio sample by moving the slider from left (should result in weak consequences) to right (should result in strong consequences) to the position that you find most appropriate.     You can always hover your mouse over  Unacceptability and Demand for Consequences in the following pages to display the definition again.

column177: G04Q12. Are you familiar with the following definition of hate speech?     "Ascribing negative attributes or deficiencies to groups of individuals because they are members of a group (e.g. all poor people are stupid) is regarded as hate speech. It combines any hateful comment toward groups because of race, political opinion, sexual orientation, gender, social status, health condition or similar."
column178: G58Q122. Do you agree with the previous definition of hate speech?

column173: Using foul language against a group of people
Public Speech, that is expressing hate towards a specific group (like religion, sexual orientation, origin, ...)
Hate speech for me means generalizing about certain groups of people in a bad and hurtful way
Spreading hate against anyone else
Publicly expressing feelings of hatred towards a specific person or group of people

column180: For some of the Audio Samples it would have been great if you could slow the speed down.

column173: hate speech intends to harass a group of people based on racists, sexist or other negative connotations attributes
Statements that directly discriminate against other people or groups of people
If someone agitates against a person or a group of people using insults and/or spreading lies, with the intend to harm the person or group of people
Using harmful and hateful speech against marginalized groups
Under the guise of anonymity, some people show their true character on the Internet
Insulting and harmful speech oriented towards someone due to their physiological/ethnical/sexual traits.
Language that discriminates certain groups of people or individuals with the added intention of spreading the message
Hurtful expression of thoughts stemming from a skewed sense of society which could lead to horrific consequences
Purposefully hurting or discriminating another person or group by calling them names or reproducing stereotypes
column180: I did have difficulties understanding some of the statements acustically or didn't know exactly what some slang words meant, which may have resulted in a lower rating of unacceptability for that specific statement.

column173: It's the expression of hate towards someone based on their race, skin color, religion...
An attack on someone or unsolicited criticism towards someone based on their looks, personality, race and ethnicity or other features
column180:
On the definition of hate speed: I chose "no" because I agree, but I think it's too narrow
On me encountering hate speech: This is based on me encountering it in real life as I do not spend a lot of time on social media



You might want to add questions on social media use and the respondents own ethnicity and political orientation, might be interesting

column173: Inhumane statements
Hate speech is narrow-minded, egotistical expression that aggressively or passively targets individuals or groups based on their characteristics, often exploiting emotional biases.
Hate speech is an aggressive, hurting and non constructive way of communication and is driven by the interest to hurt others and defend the own opinion, not to solve an issue.
Untrue or unreasonable things people say explicitly to hurt somebody in a overproportional and emotional way.
